{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "fra-collection-2026-04-29",
    "name": "Formie REST API",
    "description": "REST API endpoints for the LindemannRock Formie REST API plugin.\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Import this collection and the `Formie REST API` environment file.\n2. Set `base_url` in the environment to your site URL (e.g. `https://yoursite.com`, no trailing slash).\n3. Set `api_key` (and `signing_secret` if that key has HMAC signing enabled).\n4. Pick the environment from Postman's top-right dropdown and run any request.\n\nTo test a different key (Primary, Limited, or Test), just paste a different value into `api_key` — there is one environment, not one per key.\n\n**HMAC signing:** the collection-level pre-request script signs every request automatically and stores the timestamp + signature as collection variables (`hmac_ts`, `hmac_sig`) which the request headers reference. If `signing_secret` is empty, both vars are set to empty strings (server ignores them when the key doesn't require signing).\n\n**Test endpoints** are only accessible when `devMode = true` on the server.\n\nSee the plugin README for endpoint reference and signing details.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "apikey",
    "apikey": [
      { "key": "key", "value": "X-API-Key", "type": "string" },
      { "key": "value", "value": "{{api_key}}", "type": "string" },
      { "key": "in", "value": "header", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Collection-level HMAC signing — runs before every request.",
          "// If `signing_secret` is set on the active environment, computes",
          "// X-Timestamp + X-Signature and stores them as collection variables",
          "// (referenced by each request's Headers tab). If `signing_secret` is",
          "// empty, sets empty strings — the server ignores these headers for",
          "// keys that don't require signing.",
          "",
          "const secret = pm.environment.get('signing_secret') || '';",
          "",
          "if (!secret) {",
          "    pm.collectionVariables.set('hmac_ts', '');",
          "    pm.collectionVariables.set('hmac_sig', '');",
          "    return;",
          "}",
          "",
          "const lib = require('crypto-js');",
          "const ts = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000).toString();",
          "",
          "// Build path+query directly from the Postman Url object — avoids",
          "// `new URL(pm.request.url.toString())` which throws because toString()",
          "// returns the raw template ({{base_url}}/...) before variable resolution.",
          "const rawPath = pm.request.url.getPath() || '/';",
          "const rawQuery = pm.request.url.getQueryString() || '';",
          "// Resolve any {{vars}} the user put inside path or query (e.g. {{form_id}})",
          "const path = pm.variables.replaceIn(rawPath);",
          "const query = pm.variables.replaceIn(rawQuery);",
          "// Sort query params alphabetically before signing. The origin sits behind",
          "// Cloudflare, which normalizes (sorts) the query string before Craft sees",
          "// it — so the signature must be computed over the sorted order to match",
          "// what the server receives, regardless of the order the params were typed.",
          "const sortedQuery = query ? query.split('&').sort().join('&') : '';",
          "const pathQ = path + (sortedQuery ? '?' + sortedQuery : '');",
          "",
          "const body = pm.request.body && pm.request.body.raw ? pm.request.body.raw : '';",
          "const base = `${pm.request.method}\\n${pathQ}\\n${ts}\\n${body}`;",
          "const sig = lib.HmacSHA256(base, secret).toString(lib.enc.Hex);",
          "",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('hmac_ts', ts);",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('hmac_sig', sig);"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    { "key": "hmac_ts", "value": "" },
    { "key": "hmac_sig", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Production API",
      "description": "Public REST endpoints (`/api/v1/formie/*`). Require any valid API key. The server filters out incomplete and spam submissions automatically.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List forms",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('Response is JSON', function () { pm.response.to.be.json; });",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('success is true', function () { pm.expect(json.success).to.eql(true); });",
                  "pm.test('data is an array', function () { pm.expect(json.data).to.be.an('array'); });",
                  "pm.test('meta.total is a number', function () { pm.expect(json.meta.total).to.be.a('number'); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "X-Timestamp", "value": "{{hmac_ts}}" },
              { "key": "X-Signature", "value": "{{hmac_sig}}" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/formie/forms?limit=100&offset=0",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "formie", "forms"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "limit", "value": "100" },
                { "key": "offset", "value": "0" },
                { "key": "status", "value": "enabled", "disabled": true }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
